whole When they carried her into the courtyard he remained in the At one point I was talking with an acquaintance about Edik From her I learned that his wife was a dressmaker his mother is Russian he doesn't have a father and that he's been convicted Well this will be his third and I hope last He beat his wife she was eternally coming to work with His wife was an Armenian by the name of The others who were detained well they're little You really can't call them beasts they're just little They were robots carrying out someone else's will because at the investigation they all said I don't understand how I could have done that I was out of my But we know that they were won around to it and prepared for it that's why they did In the name of Allah in the name of the Koran in the name of propagating Islam that's holy to them that's why they did everything they were commanded to Because I saw they didn't have minds of their own I'm not talking about their level of cultural sophistication or any higher No education they work have a slew of children without the means to raise them properly they crowd them in like at the temporary housing and apparently they were promised that if they slaughtered the Armenians they would receive So off they Many of them explained their participation saying they promised us Among them was one who genuinely I am sure that he repented from the heart and that he just despised himself after the He worked at a children's home an Azerbaijani he has two children and his wife works at the children's home Everything that they acquired everything that they have they earned by their own labor and wasn't inherited from parents or And he said I didn't need anything I just don't know how I ended up in that it was like some hand was guiding I had no will of my own I had no strength no masculine dignity And the whole time I kept repeating Now you imagine that someone did the same to your young wife right before your own He sat there and just But that leader in the Eskimo dogskin coat was not He performed a marvelous disappearing act but I think that they'll get onto him they just have to work a little because that Vadim that boy according to his grandfather is in touch with the young person who taught him what to do how to cover his He was constantly exchanging jackets with other boys he knew and those he didn't either and other things as well and changed himself like a chameleon so they wouldn't get onto him but he was That one in the Eskimo dogskin coat was at the Gambarians' after Aleksandr Gambarian was He came in and said Let's go enough you've spilled enough blood Maybe Karina doesn't know this but the reason they didn't finish her off was that they were hoping to take her home with I heard this from Aunt Tanya and her sons the Kasumovs who were in the courtyard near the They liked her very much and they had decided to take her to home with When Karina came to at one point she doesn't remember this yet this the neighbors old me and she saw that there was no one around her she started crawling to the They saw that she was still alive and came back they were already at the third entryway on their way to the Gambarians' They came back and started beating her to finish If she had not come to she would have sustained lesser bodily injuries they would have beat her An older woman from our building Aunt Nazan an Azerbaijani all but lay on top of Karina crying and pleading that they leave her alone but they flung her The woman's grown sons were right nearby they picked her up in their hands and led her She howled and cried out loudly and swore God is on Earth he sees everything and He won't forgive There was another woman too Aunt Fatima a sick aging woman from the first floor she's already Mountain dwellers and Azerbaijanis too have a custom If men are fighting they throw a scarf under their feet to stop But they trampled her scarf and sent her To trample a scarf is tantamount to trampling a woman's Now that the investigation is going on now that a lot is behind us and we have gotten back to being ourselves a little I think about how could these events that are now called the Sumgait tragedy happen How did they come about How did it start Could it have been avoided Well it's clear that without a signal without permission from the top leadership it would not have All the same I'm not afraid to say this the Azerbaijanis let other worthy people take no offense the better representatives of their nations let them take no offense but the Azerbaijanis in their majority are a people who are kept in line only by fear of the law fear of retribution for what they have And when the law said that they could do all that like unleashed dogs who were afraid they wouldn't have time to do everything they threw themselves from one thing to the next so as to be able to get more done to snatch a bit The smell of the danger was already in the air on February You could tell that something was going to And everyone who had figured it out took steps to avoid running into those Many left for their dachas got plane tickets for the other end of the country just got as far away as their legs would carry February was a I was teaching my third The director came into my classroom and said that I should let the children out that there had been a call from the City Party Committee asking that all teachers gather for a meeting at Lenin Well I excused the children and there were few teachers left at school altogether three women the director and six or seven The rest had already gone We got to Lenin Square and there were a great many people This was around five thirty or six in the evening no They were saying all kinds of rubbish up on the podium and the crowd below was supporting them stormily They spoke over the microphone about what had happened in Kafan a few days earlier and that the driver of a bus going to some district had recently thrown a small Azerbaijani child off the The speaker affirmed that he was an eyewitness that he had seen it crowd started to rage Death to the Armenians They must be killed Then a woman went up on I didn't see the woman because people were clinging to the podium like I could only hear The woman introduced herself as coming from Kafan and said that the Armenians cut her daughters' breasts off and called Sons avenge my daughters That was A portion of the people on the square took off running in the direction of the factories toward the beginning of Lenin We stood there about an Then the director of School spoke he gave a very nationalist He said Brother Muslims kill the Armenians This he repeated every other When he said this the crowd supported him stormily whistling and shouting Karabagh He said Karabagh has been our territory my whole life long Karabagh is my How can you tear out my heart As though an Azerbaijani would die without It's our territory the Armenians will never see The Armenians must be From time immemorial Muslims have cleansed the land of infidel Armenians from time immemorial that's the way nature created it that every to years the Azerbaijanis should cleanse the land of By filth he meant I heard Before that I hadn't been listening to the speeches Many people spoke and I stood with my back to the podium talking shop with the other teachers and somehow it all went right by it didn't penetrate that in fact something serious was taking Then when one of our teachers said Listen to what he's saying listen to what idiocy he's spouting we That was the speech of that Before that we listened to the woman's Right then in our group there were nine of us the mood changed and the subject of conversation and all school matters were Our director of studies for whom I had great respect he's an Azerbaijani Before that I had considered him an upstanding and worthy person if there was a need to obtain leave we had asked him he seemed like a good So he tells me Lyuda you know that besides you there are no Armenians on the square If they find ou