 how people in Sumgait saved their lives their honor and their children any way they Where it was possible the Armenians fought My father's first cousin Armen lives in Block They found out by phone from one of the victims what was going on in The Armenians in that building all called one another immediately and all of them armed themselves with axes knives even with muskets and went up to the They took their infants with them and their old women who had been in bed for God knows how many months they got them right out of their beds and took everyone They hooked electricity up to the trap door to the roof and waited ready to Then they took the daughter of the school board director hostage she's an Azerbaijani who lived in their They called the school board director and told her that if she didn't help them the Armenians on the roof to escape alive and unharmed she'd never see her daughter I'm sure of course that Armenians would never lay a hand on a woman it was just the only thing that could have saved them at the She called the The Armenians made a deal with the local police to go into Two armored personnel carriers and soldiers were summoned They surrounded the entryway and led everyone down from the roof and off to the side from the armored personnel carriers was a crowd that was on its way to the building at that very moment into Block That's how they defended I heard that our neighbors Roman and Sasha Gambarian They're big strong Their father was And I heard that the brothers put up a strong defense and lost their father but were able to save their One of the neighbors told me that after it happened when they were looking for the criminals on March to and detaining everyone they suspected people hid people in our entryway maybe people who were injured or perhaps The neighbors themselves were afraid to go there and when they went with the soldiers into our basement they are supposed to have found Azerbaijani I don't know how Even if they had been wounded and put down there after two days they would have died from loss of blood or infection that basement was filled with I heard this from the And later when I was talking with the investigators the subject came up and they confirmed I know too that for several hours the basement was used to store objects stolen from our And our neighbor carried out our carpet along with the rest he stole it for himself posing as one of the Everyone was taking his own share and the neighbor took his too and carried it And when we came back when everything seemed to have calmed down he returned it saying that it was the only thing of ours he had managed to Raya's husband and father defended The Trdatovs defended themselves and so did other Armenian To be sure there were Azerbaijani victims although we'll never hear anything about For some reason our government doesn't want to say that the Armenians were not just victims but that they defended the honor of their sisters and mothers In the TV show Pozitsiya Viewpoint a military man an officer said that the Armenians did virtually nothing to defend But that's not important the truth will come out So that's the price we paid those three For three days our courage our bravery and our humanity was It was those three days and not the years and dozens of years we had lived before them that showed what we've become what we grew up to Those three days showed who was On that I will conclude my narrative on the Sumgait It should be said that it's not over yet the trials are still ahead of us and the punishments received by those who so violated us who wanted to make us into nonhumans will depend on our position and on the work of the investigators the Procuracy and literally of every person who lent his hand to the investiga That's the price we paid to live in Armenia to not fear going out on the street at night to not be afraid to say we're Armenians and to not fear speaking our native October Yerevan reference for The Sumgait Tragedy Pogroms against Arme